# Foundations
ax1 A thing either exists or it does not
ax2 If something exists then it has at least one property
ax3 Two things are identical if and only if they share all properties

# Inference
th1 Given {ax2} and {ax3} two things with different properties are not identical
th2 Given {ax1} a thing that does not exist has no properties
th3 Given {th2} and {ax3} nonexistence is unique

# Application
def1 Let "zero" be the concept of nothing
th4 Given {def1} and {ax1} zero exists as a concept
th5 Given {th4} and {ax2} zero has at least one property
th6 Given {th1} and {th5} zero is distinguishable from any other concept

# This reference is broken on purpose — the LSP should flag it
err1 Given {ax99} this should show an error
